    {
      "title": "Complex Sentences (الجملة المركبة)",
      "titleArabic": "الجملة المركبة",
      "content": [
        "Complex sentences contain a main clause and one or more subordinate clauses.",
        "Subordinate clauses can function as subject, predicate, adjective (صفة), or adverb (حال)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "جملة في محل رفع خبر - sentence as predicate",
        "جملة في محل نصب حال - sentence as circumstantial",
        "جملة في محل جر صفة - sentence as adjective",
        "جملة صلة الموصول - relative clause"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "الطَّالِبُ يَدْرُسُ فِي الْغُرْفَةِ", "english": "The student is studying in the room (sentence predicate)" },
        { "arabic": "جَاءَ وَهُوَ يَضْحَكُ", "english": "He came while laughing (circumstantial clause)" },
        { "arabic": "رَأَيْتُ رَجُلًا يَقْرَأُ", "english": "I saw a man reading (adjectival clause)" },
        { "arabic": "الَّذِي نَجَحَ مُجْتَهِدٌ", "english": "The one who succeeded is diligent (relative clause)" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Grammatical Position of Clauses",
      "titleArabic": "الموقع الإعرابي للجمل",
      "content": [
        "Clauses take grammatical positions within sentences based on their function.",
        "Understanding clause positions is essential for advanced Arabic analysis."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "الجملة الخبرية - predicate clause (في محل رفع)",
        "الجملة الحالية - circumstantial clause (في محل نصب)",
        "الجملة الوصفية - adjectival clause (تابعة لما قبلها)",
        "جملة جواب الشرط - answer to conditional"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "أَبُوهُ سَافَرَ", "english": "His father traveled (sentence as predicate)" },
        { "arabic": "خَرَجَ وَالشَّمْسُ طَالِعَةٌ", "english": "He went out while the sun was rising" },
        { "arabic": "مَرَرْتُ بِرَجُلٍ يُصَلِّي", "english": "I passed by a man praying" },
        { "arabic": "إِنْ تَدْرُسْ تَنْجَحْ", "english": "If you study, you will succeed" }
      ]
    }
  ],
